se professionals construct a vital value chain. Highlighting the role of "pioneer entrepreneurs"-who carve out space for radical, new product categories-Khaire illustrates how creative professionals influence our sense of value, shifting consumer behavior and our culture in deep, surprising ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aArtsxEconomic aspects. 0aArtsxMarketing. 0aCultural industries. 0aEntrepreneurship. 4acreative industries. 4acreators. 4acultural change. 4acultural goods. 4adigitalization. 4aentrepreneurship. 4aintermediaries. 4amarkets. 4anovel artworks. 4aradical innovation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Consumer Behavior.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503603080zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503603080423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503603080.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles